+# ChatOps config (Redis-backed, hot reload)
+
+## Keys
+
+Allowed chat id:
+- `cfg:chatops:allowed_chat_id` (string)
+
+Admins allowlist:
+- `cfg:chatops:admins` (set of telegram user ids)
+
+Two-person rule:
+- `cfg:chatops:two_person_clear` = 1/0
+- `cfg:chatops:two_person_window_s` = seconds (min 60)
+
+## Examples
+
+```bash
+redis-cli SET cfg:chatops:allowed_chat_id "-1001234567890"
+redis-cli SADD cfg:chatops:admins "11111111" "22222222"
+redis-cli SET cfg:chatops:two_person_clear "1"
+redis-cli SET cfg:chatops:two_person_window_s "300"
+```
+
+## Fail-closed
+
+If `cfg:chatops:admins` is empty and `TELEGRAM_ADMIN_USER_IDS` is empty,
+no one can execute ChatOps commands.
+
+Same for allowed chat id.
+